3 amended to read:
4 13-3106 (1) After consideration of the application and the evidence,
5 if the board finds that the project described in the application is
6 eligible and that state assistance is in the best interest of the state,
7 the application shall be approved, except that:
8 (a) An an approval of an application submitted because of the
9 requirement in subdivision (1)(c) of section 13-3103 is a temporary
10 approval. If the general obligation bond issue is subsequently approved
11 by the voters of the political subdivision, the approval by the board
12 becomes permanent. If the general obligation bond issue is not approved
13 by such voters, the temporary approval shall become void; and .
14 (b) An approval of an application submitted because of the
15 requirement in subdivision (1)(f) of section 13-3103 is a temporary
16 approval. If a building permit for the eligible sports arena facility is
17 issued within twenty-four months of the temporary approval, the approval
18 by the board becomes permanent. If a building permit is not issued within
19 twenty-four months of the temporary approval, the temporary approval
20 shall become void.
21 (2) In determining whether state assistance is in the best interest
22 of the state, the board shall consider the fiscal and economic capacity
23 of the applicant to finance the local share of the project.
24 (3) A majority of the board members constitutes a quorum for the
25 purpose of conducting business. All actions of the board shall be by a
26 majority vote of all the board members, one of whom must be the Governor.
27 Sec. 3. Original section 13-3106, Reissue Revised Statutes of
